CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Motor Vehicle Administration – Identification Cards, Licenses, and Permits
3 – Repeal of Color Photograph Requirement
4 FOR the purpose of repealing the requirement that the photograph included on an
5 identification card, a driver’s license, or a moped operator’s permit issued by the
6 Motor Vehicle Administration be in color; and generally relating to the Motor Vehicle
7 Administration and identification card, license, and permit requirements.
8 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
9 Article – Transportation
10 Section 12–301(a)
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
13 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
14 Article – Transportation
15 Section 12–301(g)(2)(v), 16–111.1(d)(2)(iv), and 16–122(d)(3)(v)
16 Annotated Code of Maryland
17 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
18 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
19 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
