2 HOUSE BILL 248
1 Article – Transportation
2 12–301.
3 (a) On application, the Administration shall issue an identification card to any
4 applicant who:
5 (1) Is a resident of this State;
6 (2) Does not have a driver’s license;
7 (3) Presents a birth certificate or other proof of age and identity acceptable
8 to the Administration;
9 (4) Provides satisfactory documentary evidence that the applicant has
10 lawful status;
11 (5) (i) Provides satisfactory documentary evidence that the applicant
12 has a valid Social Security number by presenting the applicant’s Social Security
13 Administration account card or, if the Social Security Administration account card is not
14 available, any of the following documents bearing the applicant’s Social Security number:
15 1. A current W–2 form;
16 2. A current SSA–1099 form;
17 3. A current non–SSA–1099 form; or
18 4. A current pay stub with the applicant’s name and Social
19 Security number on it; or
20 (ii) Provides satisfactory documentary evidence that the applicant is
21 not eligible for a Social Security number; and
22 (6) Presents a completed application for an identification card on a form
23 furnished by the Administration.
24 (g) (2) The card shall contain:
25 (v) A [color] photograph of the applicant taken by the procedure that
26 the Administration requires;
27 16–111.1.
28 (d) (2) A noncommercial Class A, B, C, or M license shall include:

HOUSE BILL 248 3
1 (iv) A [color] photograph of the applicant that is taken in accordance
2 with a procedure that the Administration requires;
3 16–122.
4 (d) Each identification card, moped operator’s permit, and license to drive issued
5 or renewed in accordance with this section shall:
6 (3) Be of the size and design that the Administration requires,
7 tamperproof, to the extent possible, and contain:
8 (v) A [color] photograph of the applicant taken by the procedure that
9 the Administration requires;
10 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
11 October 1, 2026.
